AccordingtoMsFrearsatLionsheadLaw,commercialanddisputeresolutionlawyerscouldbeoutofajobwithinten&nbsp;years.虽然很明显区块链是一种会影响法律行业的技术，但影响仍然不明朗。根据LionsheadLaw的Frears女士的说法，商业和争议解决律师可能会在十年内失业。“Oncerealservicesareputintoblockchain,theroleofalawyertododuediligenceaboutthegoodorservices,tocheckwhatcanbeofferedunderacontract,preparethetermsandpresentthemtoapurchaserisnegatedentirely,”shesuggests,emphasisingthattheadditionofartificialintelligencewillmeanthefieldsofbankinglaw,financialserviceslaw,litigationsupportandparalegalswillbe&nbsp;obsolete.“一旦真正的服务被纳入区块链，律师对商品或服务进行尽职调查，检查合同可以提供什么，准备条款并将其呈现给购买者的角色完全被否定，”她建议，强调增加人工智能将意味着银行法，金融服务法，诉讼支持和律师助理等领域将过时。虽然区块链是一种会影响法律行业的技术，但影响仍然不明朗Lawyers,shesays,are“bycomparisonanexpensiveandfallibleresource,withcreakysystemsandleakydatabasesthatarepronetobeing&nbsp;hacked”.她说，律师“相比之下，这是一种昂贵且易错的资源，其中包含易受攻击的系统和漏洞数据库”。ButWilliamAkmanatMorrison&amp;Foersterbelievesthatcomplicatedlegalesewillmakeitextremelydifficultforcertainlegalagreementstobecompletelyautomated,withouttheneedfora&nbsp;lawyer.但Morrison＆Foerster的WilliamAkman认为，复杂的法律术语将使某些法律协议极难完全自动化，而不需要律师。MrMaughangivestheexampleofsmartcontractsneedingtobepresentedinawaythatisunderstandablebythepersonsigningit,andthatmuchofthecontractwillincludesubjectivestatements,suchas“XwillmakereasonableeffortstodoY”,bothofwhichmaybedifficulttoautomate.Heenvisagesahybridoftechnologyandlawyerwithinsmartcontracts,wherebysomepartsofacontractcanbefullyautomatedsuchasaservicelevelagreementwithanITcompany,butotherpartsneedahuman&nbsp;element.Maughan先生给出了智能合约的例子，这种合同需要以签署人可以理解的方式呈现，并且合同的大部分将包括主观陈述，例如“X将做出合理的努力来做Y”，两者都是这可能很难实现自动化。他设想在智能合约中混合使用技术和律师，合同的某些部分可以完全自动化，例如与IT公司达成服务级别协议，但其他部分需要人为因素。Regardless,thereismovementawayfromlawyers,sofewerhourstobill.However,MrDerrickatKennedysbelievesthisisanecessarymovethatlawfirmsneedtoembrace.“We’veseenclaimsdropwithourtechnologyandclientsonlyusinglawyerswhentheyneedto,”hesays,addingthatworkonhigh-endlegalissueswillstillberequired.“Whatwe’reessentiallysayingtoyounglawyersisthattheworl